At the tail end of our reno and we’re surviving! 😵‍💫🫠🙂

Gonna be real with you and say that renovating is not for the faint of heart. We are mentally and physically EXHAUSTED. From morning to night, every day, we are working on the house. All while working, going to doctors appointments, finding time for each other and ourselves, and just dealing with all the unexpected things life throws at you. 

If Corbin wasn’t the most organized and dedicated person on the planet I would have thrown in the towel 😂 

We bought this fixer upper after we got married with the dream of making it our own. This is by far one of the biggest challenges we’ve taken on but I know the reward will be so worth it ❤️

#homerenovation #fixerupper #remodeling

2022 was tough but I’m proud of my progress! 

This is what a year of an RA flare up looks like. Muscle atrophy, weight loss, hair loss, adverse medical reactions, eyes swollen shut, level 10 pain, and lots of judgmental looks from others. 

I used to think this was my weakest point in life but looking back it was most definitely when I showed the most strength💪🏼

So much gratitude to @chadlanders for guiding me as I eased back into working out and modifying exercises to my needs. Each time I left the gym I felt stronger and more confident, so thank you for helping me lay a new foundation 🫶🏼

And to everyone who checked on me and sent me loving messages. Can’t tell you how impactful they were when I was in some really low places. 

I’m now heavier than when I started and feel like a different person. So happy my body has the weight and muscle it needs to fight for me!

2023 goal is to build more upper body strength and to continue to treat my body with the respect it deserves ❤️

If you also have an autoimmune condition or deal with chronic pain I hope this helps show you that there is light at the end of the tunnel ❤️

I hope everyone had a good holiday ❤️ Now that we’re heading into the new year I’ve been thinking about where I want my contributions to go. If you’re looking for a foundation to support that actually makes a big difference, I’ve found an amazing one!

I talked about @conquercancerfoundation here before because they really are doing great things for people all over the world. They fund research for every type of cancer and their mission is to accelerate breakthroughs in life saving research. 

I invite you to donate to this incredible cause using the link in my bio in honor or in memory of someone you love💕 Make sure to give them a follow and show them some love! #sponsored

I felt really lucky to spend the holidays with people I love this year but I know that wasn’t the case for everyone 💔 Many couldn’t celebrate with loved ones who were lost to cancer. Everyone has been impacted by cancer in some way but we can help make huge changes by supporting the @conquercancerfoundation. They are really working to give quality care for patients all over the world and our donation helps fund life saving research! 

Swipe up or click the link in my bio to donate and give them a follow to show your support. It’s a great way to give back and end the year 🥰❤️#conquercancer

Every NYE I write out what I’ve learned during the past 12 months, what made me happy, what made me unhappy, what I want to do more of, less of, my successes… I write out wellness goals, work goals, life goals, and I check in on my list throughout the year. 

They’re not resolutions per se, but I believe it’s important to have an honest breakdown of where I’m at. I love looking back and seeing which direction my path went down. How life shifted. How plans changed. 

2022 was a year of triumph for me. Through some extremely painful months I came out on the other side. Thought patterns and old habits were rewired and I am physically a different person than I was last year. My pain level is at its lowest and I am honestly so proud of the hard work I put in to get there! 

Building our home has been at the center of 2022 and has taught us so many lessons. I cannot wait to finally start hosting our epic game nights in 2023😍

Grateful to everyone who added their light into my life this past year! For the experiences and opportunities. To my unbelievable husband who is my biggest supporter and this year’s MVP. And to all of YOU who have left me the kindest words of encouragement! 

2023 I hope to continue to help others, heal myself, and live in my purpose.

Wishing you all health, love, and expansion! ❤️ 

And if you had a difficult year then remember that “New beginnings are often disguised as painful endings” Lao Tzu ❤️
